article_title: Celebrating the state of children's health in R.I.

article_metadata.description: PROVIDENCE, R.I. — The fact that Rhode Island's RIte Care program ranks tops in the country, and nearly 97 percent of the state's children now have health insurance will be cause for celebration Monday. So too, are improved health outcomes for children.A host of public officials, community leaders and health-care advocates are scheduled to gather at the Rhode Island Kids Count 15th Celebration of Children's Health Luncheon at the Providence Marriott.  Rhode Island now
article_metadata.author: Karen Lee Ziner
